cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and computational analysis of written history on Wikipedia. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also a likely category as the paper involves the analysis of a large corpus of text from Wikipedia. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper involves the identification and analysis of temporal focal points in historical timelines. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper involves the analysis of historical narratives across different language editions of Wikipedia. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses biases in the portrayal of national histories on Wikipedia.
